snippet.textDisplay:
I don't watch TV, but I do view YouTube and I've seen Carpool Karaoke and enjoyed it. But the fact that someone being filmed in a car is not driving the car doesn't really affect my world. However, it does seem to affect the lives of way too many people (and I thought my life was meaningless!).


It just shows you how terribly shallow people are that this is a big concern to them. How invested must they be in something that is, frankly, trivial to be upset when they find out it isn't what they thought it was. It's a real pity they aren't as invested in things that matter like: feeding the poor, housing the homeless, climate change, and just generally being nice to each. (You can't really blame the "newspapers" because they have to provide the "news" that the shallow population WANTS to see, not what they NEED to see.)


Why am I commenting? Why am I invested in something so trivial? When you attack someone who spends their time entertaining others, including yourselves, because they don't do something just the way you like it -- I DON'T THINK THAT IS TRIVIAL! I know that the old sayings are thought of as quaint and outdated, but in most cases they made for a much nicer world. IF YOU DON'T HAVE SOMETHING NICE TO SAY ABOUT SOMEONE, DON'T SAY ANYTHING AT ALL!



James Corden has provided me with a lot of entertainment over the years and I'll probably never meet him, so this is one way I can say "Thank You". "You make me smile and laugh!" is the best compliment I can give anyone. Keep up the great work - Have Fun! (and don't let the bastards get you down!)
